
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `infobrowser` baraye didan va gashtan dar etela'at dastoor-ha estefade mishavad. Mesle yek ketabche-ye rahnama, vali dar terminal.  In dastoor shoma ra komak mikonad ta behtar dark konid har dastoor che kar mikonad va che gozine-haee darad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `infobrowser` --> 💻 Baz kardan rahnama-ye dastoor-ha be soorate grafiki (agar dastras bashad).
    🔹 `infobrowser --help`  --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye sade dastoor `infobrowser`.
    🔹 Dar dakhel `infobrowser`, az kelid-haye harekat (arrow keys), `n` (baraye safhe-ye badi), va `p` (baraye safhe-ye ghabeli) estefade konid.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ infobrowser

    🔹 Baz kardan safhe-ye asli `infobrowser`.

    $ infobrowser ls

    🔹 Baz kardan etela'at marboot be dastoor `ls`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ infobrowser bash

    🔹 In dastoor etela'at ra darbareye `bash` (yek noe shell dar linux) namayesh midahad, ke dar an tozihat, dastoorat va gozine-haee ke mitavanid estefade konid vojood darad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `infobrowser` command is used to view and navigate command information pages. It's like a manual, but within the terminal or in a graphical browser, providing a detailed explanation of commands and their options.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `infobrowser` --> 💻 Opens the command documentation in a graphical browser (if available).
    🔹 `infobrowser --help` --> ❓ Displays basic help information about the `infobrowser` command itself.
    🔹 Within `infobrowser`, use arrow keys, `n` (for next page), and `p` (for previous page) for navigation.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ infobrowser

    🔹 Opens the main `infobrowser` page.

    $ infobrowser ls

    🔹 Opens the information page for the `ls` command.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ infobrowser bash

    🔹 This command displays information about `bash` (a common Linux shell), including explanations, commands, and available options.
